Inlaks, sub-Saharan Africa’s largest system integrator has expanded its operations into East Africa with the opening of a new office in Nairobi, Kenya. The company said this was in response to the increasing demand for technology-enabled and self-service financial operations in Africa including its already growing presence in Ghana, Gambia, Guinea, Sierra Leone, Cameroun, Ethiopia and Nigeria its headquarters. The MD/CEO, Inlaks Africa Operations, Femi Adeoti, said, “This is another call for Inlaks to add value to relevant sectors in East Africa. Apart from employment opportunities opened to skilled population in the region, we never retract our commitment to serve the African community to the best of our capacity. “Our vision remains to be the foremost ICT and infrastructure service provider in Sub-saharan Africa. We look forward to establishing more regional branches in other locations in Africa.” The Country general manager, East Africa, Edna Kirmuwa, said that with the well-established operations in Nairobi, it would be easier to extend Inlaks’ services to neighbouring countries. According to him, “As a major distributor of Hyosung ATM brands and Temenos banking software in Africa, our base in Kenya would definitely yield an exponential growth and a remarkable digital transformation for financial organisations we service.